HTTP:

http.request            --> returns Observable. we can subscribe() to it.


------------------------------------------------------------------

Routing:

Hash based routing  : using # anchor tag.
HTML5 based routing : browser's navigation history api (using history.pushState) {default in Angular0}

installing routes   : RouterModule.forRoot(routes) in NgModules's imports

RouterOutlet        : directive used to explain angular where in page it should apply routes.
RouterLink          : directive to use the route without page reload.

location strategy   : the way angular application parse & create path from n to route definitions.
PathLocationStrategy: HTML5 routing. (default strategy)
HashLocationStrategy: # based.

ActivatedRoute      : need to import in order to use route parameters.

CanActivate         : to guard protected component.